Note:
HIR to MongoDB Generator

Generates MongoDB queries from Runa HIR in JSON-like format.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

@Reasoning:
Public entry point for HIR to MongoDB shell query generation. Owns the
emitter lifetime so callers only need to provide the HIR root and consume
the resulting query string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a raw byte emitter, calls generate_value on the HIR root at indent
level 0, then extracts the accumulated output. Returns 0 if emitter
construction fails so callers can short-circuit.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_mongodb" takes hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate MongoDB query from HIR

    Let emitter be proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon

    If emitter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc generate_value with hir, emitter, 0

    Let output be proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter

    Return output
End Process

@Reasoning:
Central dispatcher for HIR-to-MongoDB shell syntax. MongoDB queries are JSON-
like nested values, so the same routine handles document, array, operation
sub-types and literals. Null inputs map to the MongoDB null literal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the kind tag at offset 0 of the HIR value node (1=dictionary,
2=list, 3=literal). Lists route to generate_array; literals emit the raw
byte slice at offset 8 verbatim. Dictionaries look up the "type" attribute:
"document" recurses into generate_document; the operation kinds
(query/aggregate/update/insert/delete) route to their respective emitters;
an untyped dictionary (e.g. an operator {operator,value}) is emitted as a
plain document.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_value" takes value as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate MongoDB value (document, array, literal, or operation)

    If value is equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "null"
        Return 1
    End If

    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with value, 0

    Note: kind = 3 -> literal byte slice at offset 8
    If kind is equal to 3:
        Let literal be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with value, 8
        If literal is equal to 0:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "null"
        Otherwise:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, literal
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: kind = 2 -> list
    If kind is equal to 2:
        Return proc generate_array with value, emitter, indent_level
    End If

    Note: kind = 1 -> dictionary; route on its "type" attribute
    Let type_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "type"
    Let type_value be proc dict_get with value, type_key

    If type_value is not equal to 0:
        Let is_document be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_value, "document"
        If is_document is equal to 1:
            Return proc generate_document with value, emitter, indent_level
        End If

        Note: Check for operation types
        Let is_query be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_value, "query"
        If is_query is equal to 1:
            Return proc generate_query_operation with value, emitter, indent_level
        End If

        Let is_aggregate be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_value, "aggregate"
        If is_aggregate is equal to 1:
            Return proc generate_aggregate_operation with value, emitter, indent_level
        End If

        Let is_update be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_value, "update"
        If is_update is equal to 1:
            Return proc generate_update_operation with value, emitter, indent_level
        End If

        Let is_insert be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_value, "insert"
        If is_insert is equal to 1:
            Return proc generate_insert_operation with value, emitter, indent_level
        End If

        Let is_delete be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_value, "delete"
        If is_delete is equal to 1:
            Return proc generate_delete_operation with value, emitter, indent_level
        End If
    End If

    Note: Untyped dictionary (a MongoDB $-operator map) -> emit as {"$op": value}
    Return proc generate_operator with value, emitter, indent_level
End Process

@Reasoning:
A document is the building block of MongoDB queries; it maps field names to
arbitrary nested values. The emitted form is JSON-like with field separators
to match the shell syntax.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "{", then walks the "fields" list dispatching each entry through
generate_field, separating consecutive fields with ", ". Closes with "}".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_document" takes doc as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate document: {field: value, ...}

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 123  Note: {

    Let fields_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "fields"
    Let fields be proc dict_get with doc, fields_key

    If fields is not equal to 0:
        Let field_count be proc list_size with fields
        Let index be 0

        While index is less than field_count:
            Let field be proc list_get with fields, index

            If index is greater than 0:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ", "
            End If

            proc generate_field with field, emitter, indent_level

            Set index to index plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 125  Note: }

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A document member is either a plain field (name: value) or a MongoDB
$-operator member ($op: value). The translator emits a {name,value}
dictionary for the former and an {operator,value} dictionary for the
latter, and both flavours land in the parent document's fields list. This
routine probes for the "operator" key first so $-operators rendered as a
document member keep their $-name; otherwise it falls back to the plain
field shape. The member key is quoted to match BSON serialization
conventions accepted by the shell.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the "operator" attribute; if present it is the member key, otherwise
the "name" attribute is. The key is emitted via emit_key, which is
idempotent: an unquoted identifier/operator key is wrapped in double
quotes, while a key whose first byte is already a double quote (produced by
a prior emission that the lexer then captured quote-inclusive) is emitted
verbatim so re-emission never accumulates extra quote pairs. The key is
followed by ": " and the "value" child recursed through generate_value.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_field" takes field as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate document member: "key": value

    Let operator_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operator"
    Let operator_name be proc dict_get with field, operator_key

    Let member_key be 0
    If operator_name is not equal to 0:
        Set member_key to operator_name
    Otherwise:
        Let name_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "name"
        Set member_key to proc dict_get with field, name_key
    End If

    proc emit_key with member_key, emitter
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ": "

    Let value_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "value"
    Let value be proc dict_get with field, value_key

    proc generate_value with value, emitter, indent_level

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Document member keys must be emitted with exactly one surrounding pair of
double quotes regardless of how the key string was produced. MongoDB shell
keys arrive at the translator either as bare identifiers/operators (no
quotes) or, after a prior emission round, as quote-inclusive string slices
captured by the lexer. Adding quotes unconditionally would double them on
re-emission and break round-trip idempotency; this helper makes emission a
fixed point.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If the key pointer is 0, emit an empty quoted key. Otherwise read its first
byte: if it is already a double quote (34), the key carries its own quotes
so emit it verbatim; otherwise wrap the key in a double-quote pair. Returns
1.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_key" takes key as Integer, emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a document member key with exactly one pair of double quotes

    If key is equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 34  Note: "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 34  Note: "
        Return 1
    End If

    Let first_char be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with key, 0

    If first_char is equal to 34:  Note: already starts with "
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, key
        Return 1
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 34  Note: "
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, key
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 34  Note: "

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A MongoDB $-operator node carries an operator name (e.g. "$gt") plus a
single operand value. In shell/JSON syntax it renders as a one-field
object: {"$gt": <value>}. Emitting it through this dedicated routine keeps
the operator name quoted and its operand recursed through generate_value
so nested operators ($and: [ ... ]) survive.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "{". Reads the "operator" attribute (a raw byte slice) and emits it
quoted, then ": ". Reads the "value" attribute and recurses through
generate_value. Closes with "}". Returns 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_operator" takes operator_node as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate operator object: {"$op": value}

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 123  Note: {

    Let op_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operator"
    Let op_name be proc dict_get with operator_node, op_key

    proc emit_key with op_name, emitter
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ": "

    Let value_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "value"
    Let value be proc dict_get with operator_node, value_key

    proc generate_value with value, emitter, indent_level

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 125  Note: }

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
MongoDB arrays appear inside aggregation pipelines and bulk-insert arguments;
they are JSON-style square-bracket sequences with comma-separated values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "[", walks the list by index, recurses into generate_value for each
element with a leading ", " separator on all but the first, then emits "]".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_array" takes array as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate array: [value, ...]

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 91  Note: [

    Let size be proc list_size with array
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than size:
        Let value be proc list_get with array, index

        If index is greater than 0:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ", "
        End If

        proc generate_value with value, emitter, indent_level

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 93  Note: ]

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MongoDB Operation Generation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
find() and findOne() are MongoDB's read primitives. Both accept an optional
projection document as a second argument, which the emitter must include
only when present.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the operation name (find / findOne) followed by "(", a query document
(defaulting to "{}" when null), an optional projection prefixed with ", ",
and the closing ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_query_operation" takes operation as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate find() or findOne() operation
    Note: Format: db.collection.find({query}) or db.collection.find({query}, {projection})

    Note: Get operation name
    Let op_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operation"
    Let op_name be proc dict_get with operation, op_key

    Note: Emit operation name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, op_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Note: Get and generate query document
    Let query_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "query"
    Let query be proc dict_get with operation, query_key

    If query is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_value with query, emitter, indent_level
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "{}"
    End If

    Note: Check for optional projection
    Let proj_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "projection"
    Let projection be proc dict_get with operation, proj_key

    If projection is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ", "
        proc generate_value with projection, emitter, indent_level
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41  Note: )

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
aggregate() takes a pipeline of stages. The pipeline is itself an array of
documents, so this emitter wraps the generic array generator in the
aggregate() call form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "aggregate(", recurses on the pipeline value through generate_value
(defaulting to "[]" when null), then emits ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_aggregate_operation" takes operation as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate aggregate([...]) operation
    Note: Format: db.collection.aggregate([{$stage1}, {$stage2}, ...])

    Note: Get operation name
    Let op_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operation"
    Let op_name be proc dict_get with operation, op_key

    Note: Emit operation name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, op_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Note: Get and generate pipeline array
    Let pipeline_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "pipeline"
    Let pipeline be proc dict_get with operation, pipeline_key

    If pipeline is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_value with pipeline, emitter, indent_level
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "[]"
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41  Note: )

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
updateOne, updateMany and replaceOne share a (filter, update, options)
signature where options is optional. A single emitter handles all three.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the operation name, "(", filter (defaulting to "{}"), ", " plus update
document, optional ", " plus options, then ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_update_operation" takes operation as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate updateOne(), updateMany(), or replaceOne() operation
    Note: Format: db.collection.updateOne({filter}, {update}, {options})

    Note: Get operation name
    Let op_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operation"
    Let op_name be proc dict_get with operation, op_key

    Note: Emit operation name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, op_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Note: Get and generate filter document
    Let filter_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "filter"
    Let filter be proc dict_get with operation, filter_key

    If filter is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_value with filter, emitter, indent_level
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "{}"
    End If

    Note: Get and generate update document
    Let update_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "update"
    Let update be proc dict_get with operation, update_key

    If update is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ", "
        proc generate_value with update, emitter, indent_level
    End If

    Note: Check for optional options
    Let options_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "options"
    Let options be proc dict_get with operation, options_key

    If options is not equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, ", "
        proc generate_value with options, emitter, indent_level
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41  Note: )

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
insertOne and insertMany differ only in whether documents is a single
document or an array. The same emitter handles both by passing the
documents node through generate_value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits operation name, "(", the documents value via generate_value
(defaulting to "{}" when null), then ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_insert_operation" takes operation as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate insertOne() or insertMany() operation
    Note: Format: db.collection.insertOne({document}) or db.collection.insertMany([{doc1}, {doc2}])

    Note: Get operation name
    Let op_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operation"
    Let op_name be proc dict_get with operation, op_key

    Note: Emit operation name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, op_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Note: Get and generate documents
    Let docs_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "documents"
    Let documents be proc dict_get with operation, docs_key

    If documents is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_value with documents, emitter, indent_level
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "{}"
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41  Note: )

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
deleteOne and deleteMany both take a single filter document. The emitter
shape is the simplest of the operation family.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the operation name, "(", the filter document (defaulting to "{}"),
and ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_delete_operation" takes operation as Integer, emitter as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate deleteOne() or deleteMany() operation
    Note: Format: db.collection.deleteOne({filter}) or db.collection.deleteMany({filter})

    Note: Get operation name
    Let op_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "operation"
    Let op_name be proc dict_get with operation, op_key

    Note: Emit operation name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, op_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Note: Get and generate filter document
    Let filter_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "filter"
    Let filter be proc dict_get with operation, filter_key

    If filter is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_value with filter, emitter, indent_level
    Otherwise:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "{}"
    End If

    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41  Note: )

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Dictionary and List Utilities
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The backend reads HIR attribute lookups from the kind-tagged parallel-array
dictionary emitted by the translator (kind at offset 0, size at offset 8,
keys at offset 24, values at offset 32). A local helper avoids dragging the
full Dict module into the import list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads size, keys_ptr and values_ptr from the dict header at offsets
8/24/32, then linearly scans the keys array calling string_equals against
the query key. Returns the matching value pointer or 0 when no key matches.
@End Implementation

Process called "dict_get" takes dict as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get value from dictionary by key

    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dict, 8
    Let keys_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dict, 24
    Let values_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dict, 32

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than size:
        Let current_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with keys_ptr, index multiplied by 8
        Let keys_match be proc string_equals from StringCore with current_key, key

        If keys_match is equal to 1:
            Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with values_ptr, index multiplied by 8
            Return value
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Trivial accessor that reads the list-length field directly from the
kind-tagged list header (kind at offset 0, size at offset 8). Kept local
because the imported list module is not depended on here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the int64 at offset 8 of the list header.
@End Implementation

Process called "list_size" takes list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get list size

    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with list, 8
    Return size
End Process

@Reasoning:
Trivial random-access reader; lists store their item pointer array at
offset 24 of the kind-tagged header and items are int64-sized.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the items pointer from offset 24, then reads index * 8 bytes into
that array to fetch the requested entry.
@End Implementation

Process called "list_get" takes list as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get item from list by index

    Let items be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with list, 24
    Let item be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with items, index multiplied by 8
    Return item
End Process

Note: End of HIR to MongoDB Generator
